The paper deals with a dynamical process in a network, which involves the distribution of tokens among nodes. This process is related to traversals based on Eulerian circuits on a directed graph, and the paper uses sum set methods to prove its results. These topics are closely related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM), distributed systems (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), social and information networks (cs.SI), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
